    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.01413_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Greene</name>
                    <date when="1870-05-15">May 
                        15<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="superscript">th</hi></hi>/70</date>
                    </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Friend<ptr target="n0810"/></salute>
                <salute>Walt Whitman</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Your letter<ptr target="loc.01999_n1"/>
                <supplied reason="worn-away" resp="#cn" cert="high">was</supplied> welcomed of april
                15th <gap reason="illegible" quantity="7" unit="chars"/> <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#js">some</unclear>
                time ago but I <supplied reason="illegible" resp="#cn" cert="medium">have been</supplied> 
                very busy and <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#nnk">haven't</unclear>
                <gap reason="illegible" quantity="4" unit="chars"/>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#kk">time<!--shively--></unclear> to
                answer it before. It gives me great pleasure to receive a letter from you <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#kk">and be able<!--shively--></unclear> to
                hear the <gap reason="illegible" extent="1 word"/> on <gap reason="illegible" extent="2 words"/>
                <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#aja" cert="low">well</unclear>.</p>
            <p>My Father<ptr target="n0811"/> died May 2<hi rend="superscript">nd</hi> and was
                buried on the 4<hi rend="superscript"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi> I was in
                    <name>Syracuse</name> a few days before he died to see him for the Last time
                alive <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#kk">He waited</unclear>
                anxiously for the <gap reason="illegible" extent="1 word"/> and welcomed death as a
                friend to take him 
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_vm.01414_large.jpg" type="verso"/> 
                to a better country</p>
            <p>he Died as he has always lived a good man &amp; a Christian.</p>
            <p>The Syracuse Journal says A Good Man Gone—</p>
            <p>For years Henry Wilson has proved <gap reason="illegible" extent="1 word"/>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#kk">ho</unclear>nesty and Efficiency as
                    <gap reason="illegible" extent="2 words"/> with itinerary <gap reason="illegible" extent="2 words"/>ing and <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#aja">repairing</unclear>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#aja">Clocks</unclear> <gap reason="illegible" extent="1 word"/> always earned
                    an<gap reason="illegible" extent="1 word"/> thought the <gap reason="deletion" extent="2 words"/>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#nnk">he</unclear> could give to God,
                    <gap reason="illegbile" extent="2 words"/> his <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#nnk">fellow men</unclear>. The poor, especially wil
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="1 word"/> his
                kindly words and services <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#nnk">The
                    meaning</unclear> of the first is <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#aja" cert="medium">blessed</unclear>."</p>
            <p>My Mother<ptr target="loc.01997_n3"/> is <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#aja">not very</unclear>
                well this summer <gap reason="illegible" extent="1 word"/></p>
            <p>Little Walt<ptr target="loc.01996_n2"/> <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#kk">and the</unclear>
                rest of my family are <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_vm.01415_large.jpg" type="recto"/> all well.<ptr target="loc.01997_n4"/> he is quite a boy now and can <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#nnk">run</unclear>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#nnk">out doors</unclear> and get into
                all kinds of mischief.</p>
            <p>It is a beautiful quiet day here today and I would like it very much if <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#nnk">we</unclear> could be together to day
                and take a pleasant stroll through the green Fields and Woods.</p>
            <p>Write as soon as convenient</p>
            <p>With Love to you</p>
            <closer> 
                <salute>Yours</salute>
                <signed>B. H. Wilson</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc_vm.01416_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <note resp="#ww" type="editorial">BH Wilson</note>
        </body>
